whistle that is [INAUDIBLE] in--

00:21:45.472 --> 00:21:46.918
[TRAFFIC NOISE]

00:21:46.918 --> 00:21:51.930
- In Belterra, the town
in the Amazon, but now

00:21:51.930 --> 00:21:54.330
it's aligned with school time.

00:21:54.330 --> 00:21:58.500
They think that that's part
of the identity of the place.

00:22:01.480 --> 00:22:03.980
The installation presents
an uncanny situation

00:22:03.980 --> 00:22:06.590
that makes the familiar
foreign, and vise versa.

00:22:25.286 --> 00:22:41.222
[ROOSTER CROWING]

00:22:41.222 --> 00:22:43.610
- OK, I will jump a little.

00:22:43.610 --> 00:22:45.560
Kind of destroying
my own work, but--

00:22:48.150 --> 00:22:51.450
So you have images of--

00:22:51.450 --> 00:22:54.270
as I said, it's
like the narrative

00:22:54.270 --> 00:22:58.240
is one day in the
life of these towns,

00:22:58.240 --> 00:23:04.420
and there is still some rubber
tappers that work independently

00:23:04.420 --> 00:23:08.290
in Alberta and in Michigan.

00:23:08.290 --> 00:23:12.280
The town is part of the
Michigan Tech University,

00:23:12.280 --> 00:23:14.260
so you have students
doing field work

00:23:14.260 --> 00:23:18.030
and living there for a semester.

00:23:18.030 --> 00:23:26.380
So, and then it ends
with people exercising,

00:23:26.380 --> 00:23:31.840
and what I want to show this.

00:23:31.840 --> 00:23:36.750
So one thing-- these benches
here, I made replicas of them,

00:23:36.750 --> 00:23:42.460
and those are the benches
that are in the installation,

00:23:42.460 --> 00:23:45.930
and this is the obviously
spontaneous addition

00:23:45.930 --> 00:23:46.950
to the planned city.

00:23:46.950 --> 00:23:50.530
It's not part of the original
plan, but for some reason,

00:23:50.530 --> 00:23:54.020
most of the houses have these
benches facing to each other,

00:23:54.020 --> 00:23:56.220
and that's the place
where people socialize

00:23:56.220 --> 00:23:57.490
at the end of the day.

00:24:08.900 --> 00:24:11.720
In addition to the
videos, I did this series

00:24:11.720 --> 00:24:15.320
of 14 photographs that are
called "When Two Places Look

00:24:15.320 --> 00:24:19.490
Alike," and they are part of
the same body of the work.

00:24:19.490 --> 00:24:24.140
So I created a typological
study of the workers houses

00:24:24.140 --> 00:24:27.170
by juxtaposing fragments
of them with cut

00:24:27.170 --> 00:24:30.800
out cards that travel with
me across the hemisphere

00:24:30.800 --> 00:24:32.450
to each location.

00:24:32.450 --> 00:24:35.360
By using my hand
to hold the cards,

00:24:35.360 --> 00:24:37.820
I insert myself as a
connector of these two

00:24:37.820 --> 00:24:42.650
locations, these two places--

00:24:42.650 --> 00:24:46.530
sorry-- these two physically
distant places that share

00:24:46.530 --> 00:24:49.010
a historical background.

00:24:49.010 --> 00:24:51.320
The current
inhabitants of Alberta

00:24:51.320 --> 00:24:53.210
are totally unaware
that there is

00:24:53.210 --> 00:24:55.760
this other town in South
America that looks just

00:24:55.760 --> 00:24:57.605
like their town and vise versa.

00:25:05.680 --> 00:25:09.720
While Western industry exported
traditional New England

00:25:09.720 --> 00:25:12.570
architecture style
to the Amazon region,

00:25:12.570 --> 00:25:16.080
quintessential American
architect Frank Lloyd Wright

00:25:16.080 --> 00:25:20.580
incorporated Mayan features such
as the textile concrete block

00:25:20.580 --> 00:25:24.420
system in some of his
residential buildings

00:25:24.420 --> 00:25:28.120
built in Los Angeles
in the early 1900s.

00:25:28.120 --> 00:25:31.980
The video, "Ch'u Mayaa," was
filmed at one of these houses,

00:25:31.980 --> 00:25:36.390
the Hollyhock House, which was
designed for the feminist oil

00:25:36.390 --> 00:25:42.480
heiress, Aline Barnsdall, who
was also a patron of the arts

00:25:42.480 --> 00:25:45.540
and later donated the
house to the city.

00:25:45.540 --> 00:25:48.750
This was the piece that
I received the commission

00:25:48.750 --> 00:25:53.540
for from the city of LA for
a Geddes Foundation Pacific

00:25:53.540 --> 00:25:57.030
Standard Time LA LA.

00:25:57.030 --> 00:26:02.160
To my response to the overlooked
influence of Mayan architecture

00:26:02.160 --> 00:26:05.130
on Wright's work by
reappropriating the building

00:26:05.130 --> 00:26:07.920
as a temple and
imbuing it with a dance

00:26:07.920 --> 00:26:11.220
performance based on
gestures and postures

00:26:11.220 --> 00:26:14.790
found in ancient Mayan
pottery and murals.

00:26:14.790 --> 00:26:17.480
Through the movement
of a female performer,

00:26:17.480 --> 00:26:20.640
the house is
resignified, or claimed,

00:26:20.640 --> 00:26:23.190
as belonging to the
pre-Columbian Mesoamerican

00:26:23.190 --> 00:26:25.090
architecture lineage.

00:26:25.090 --> 00:26:27.600
The title, translated
"Maya Blue"

00:26:27.600 --> 00:26:32.640
from K'iche', one of the Mayan
languages spoken in LA today,

00:26:32.640 --> 00:26:37.590
refers to the ancient azure
pigment found in Mayan pottery

00:26:37.590 --> 00:26:41.760
and murals, well known for being
remarkably weather resistant

00:26:41.760 --> 00:26:45.779
and enduring the
passage of time.

00:26:45.779 --> 00:26:46.570
So these are just--

00:26:46.570 --> 00:26:48.430
I don't expect you
to read all of this,

00:26:48.430 --> 00:26:53.050
but it's just to show a
little bit of the reference

00:26:53.050 --> 00:27:01.980
of my research for creating
a catalog of movements,

00:27:01.980 --> 00:27:03.980
and I will play a
little bit of the video.

00:27:19.387 --> 00:27:22.369
[FLUTE PLAYING]

00:27:33.303 --> 00:27:35.788
[BIRD CHIRPING]

